defaultAleemadefault defaultShivjidefault: One of the things to look at as well is there is a big gap between doing immunisations and providing Western medicine for people with disabilities.  There are lots of things in between that.  It is looking at the impact on the community.  There are statistics on diabetes; every 20 seconds, somebody has an amputation around the world for diabetes.  If we do not do something to support those people who are having amputations, the cost to their communities is huge.  We need to look at not just the immediate health impact but the impact on the whole 
