defaultDr Shakespearedefault: Shall I go first?  As we are all well aware around this room, the Convention on the Rights of Persons with Disabilities, which so many countries have ratified, means that they have to revise their laws in line with that.  It is very easy to ratify; you could see on the day that it was first tabled not everybody but a large number of people ratified it straight away.  Of course, they are not complying.  They were not then and they are not now.  DFID working with countries to say, “Look, you have ratified; how are you going to revise your laws?  How are you going to revise your practices?  How are you going to meet your obligations?” is really important.  If we are going to do that, people are going to turn around and say, “
defaultUnited Kingdom
